com.timesten.jdbc.connectionpool
Class TimesTenPooledPreparedStatement

java.lang.Object
  com.timesten.jdbc.connectionpool.TimesTenPooledPreparedStatement
All Implemented Interfaces:
com.timesten.jdbc.TimesTenPreparedStatement, com.timesten.jdbc.TimesTenStatement, java.sql.PreparedStatement, java.sql.Statement, java.sql.Wrapper
public final class TimesTenPooledPreparedStatement
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.timesten.jdbc.TimesTenPreparedStatement

Represents a TimesTen prepared statement. This class should not be instantiated directly. Instances of this classs are manipulated via methods in the associated TimesTenPooledConnection and TimesTenConnectionPool classes.

This class implements the TimesTenPreparedStatement interface, plus some additional methods.

Any methods which are not explicitly documented behave identically to the corresponding method in TimesTenPreparedStatement.

Any individual instance of this class should not be shared amongst multiple threads.

If the connection that owns this statement has been invalidated due to a failover most methods will throw a TTCP_ERR_STMT_INVALID exception.

getLabel

public final java.lang.String getLabel()
Returns the textual label associated with this statement. The label is defined when the statement is created via one of the addPreparedStatement() methods in the TimesTenPooledConnection class.

public final java.lang.String getSql()
Returns the SQL text for this prepared statement. This can be useful for debugging or tracing.

getOptHints

public final java.lang.String[] getOptHints()
Returns the array of optimiser hints used when preparing this statement. This can be useful for debugging or tracing. If no hints were used (the usual case) then returns null.

close

public final void close()
Silently does nothing. A TimesTenPooledPreparedStatement can only be closed by the owning TimesTenPooledConnection object which in turn will only close the statement when directed to by its owning TimestenConnectionPool object, via the removePreparedStatement() method.
